      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "was mighty among his brethren.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Comp. Jacob’s blessing (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 49:8-10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): “Judah, thou—thy brethren shall praise thee, Thy hand shall be on the neck of thy foes, Thy father’s sons shall bow before thee. Sceptre shall not depart from Judah, Nor doom-staff from between his feet,” &c. (See also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 1:1-2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where Judah is divinely commissioned to lead the attack upon the Canaanites.) At the census of Moses, Judah greatly outnumbered any other single tribe (",
        "children": []
