      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Not the person, (for in person Joseph prevailed,) but the tribe of Judah. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Prevailed — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Excelled the other tribes, especially in the following privilege. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And of him — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For of him, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as the Hebrew ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ו",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "vau, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "is often used: this being a reason of the foregoing assertion, or declaration, showing wherein he did prevail. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Came the chief ruler — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The government was, by God’s promise and appointment, to be seated chiefly and most durably in that tribe, first in David and his successors, and then in the Messiah, who ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sprang out of Judah, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(",
        "children": []
