  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For Judah prevailed above his brethren,.... That is, the tribe of Judah prevailed above the rest in number, in valour, and courage, and in dignity; wherefore the genealogy is not reckoned according to birthright, but dignity and dominion; hence this genealogical account began with Judah: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because of him came the chief ruler; David and the kings of Judah, his successors; and above all, from him the Prince Messiah was to spring, and did, according to Genesis 49:10 so both the Syriac and Arabic versions read,\"out of Judah should go forth the King Messiah:\" ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "because of him came the chief ruler; David and the kings of Judah, his successors; and above all, from him the Prince Messiah was to spring, and did, according to ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 49:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " so both the Syriac and Arabic versions read,\"out of Judah should go forth the King Messiah:\" ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but the birthright was Joseph's or \"though\" (p) it was; yet Judah having the dominion and dignity, that tribe is first genealogized. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(p) Licet, ibid. (Tigurine version) ",
        "children": [
          {
